  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Vasopressor for current treatment protocols for acute traumatic brain injury can lead to
      vasoconstriction and thus cerebral hypoperfusion that can be detected with cerebral oxymetry
      as a drop in SCO2.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
